name: Warung The Ulam
address: Jl. Raya Munggu, Tanah lot, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: The fish and shrimp is ok. The cumi cumi is little hard. The chicken not suitable for individual taste. The flies everywhere. Weather is hot and humid at Mar 2024.
review 2: We stopped by for dinner at Warung The Ulam. We were warmly welcomed by the polite staff of the restaurant. Warung is surrounded by rice fields, a picturesque place. We ordered seafood sets. All the dishes are very tasty. Recommended!
review 3: One of the best Ikan Bakar places I have been to. Lovely place, good ambience, next to the rice fields, loved their bamboo cottage seating. I had a Grilled Snapper which was really yum.
review 4:
We are fresh fish lover and i know how good dish should be. The grilled fish and clamps here deserve 5 star. We have tried the more expensive grilled fish in Jimbaran and The Ulam is as tasty as those in the hype one from Jimbaran.

As far as ambience, it is great than average as you can enjoy paddy field view next to your great dish.

Moreover you will suprised with good price this place offered.
review 5: One of the most delicious Ikan bakar I've every tried. Affordable and nice ambience. I chose to sit on one of the traditional wooden hut. Memorable experience. They allow me to eat my fruits I bought outside, in their restaurant. Highly recommended. üòä

name: BARUNA SEAFOOD 88
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot No.88x, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Was in Bali for 3 weeks, went to this restaurant twice! This had my Jimbaran styled seafood craving fixed! Everything was so fresh and well seasoned, went to the other warungs bakar but nothing was as good as this one. Salmon soup was just so rich, you can skip your fish oil supplement for some time. Every dish exceeded my expectations and I will defo be coming back for more the next time around!
review 2: Really nice food and with reasonable price.  Seafoods are fresh and the tom yum soup is highly recommended!  A good restaurant to try for the local food.
review 3: Seafood here is ok. Friendly staff. I think there is Live Band after 7pm. Its just next to the busy road. Parking is quite spacious but not that big. Overall its ok to stop by and have a cheap seaffod.
review 4:
Great seafood here served in the Jimbaran style, without the Jimbaran waiting time - food was served impressively fast!

Had my doubts on the freshness given how short it took to get from kitchen to table, but as someone with a frozen shellfish allergy, I could tell it was fresh since I had no reactions after eating their grilled shrimp.

Though I imagine I wasn't dining during their peak times, I would still recommend this place for anyone wanting a decent Jimbaran seafood dinner, without having to travel all the way to South Kuta. Also happy that they serve Set Meals for individual diners, which was very convenient.

Great service, friendly and attentive wait staff, and plenty of parking for both cars and scooters.
review 5: One of the best seafood warungs in the. Area! We‚Äôre going back today for the 2th time

name: BlackDot ID (kost harian, bulanan)
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
It could be better somehow - I stayed here for a month and got a room with balcony. It was nice for the first two/three days however due to its location on the intercity highway, dust started to settle in very fast. You also can't use the balcony because opening the balcony door will immediately fill the room with more dust. Even though the housekeeper tried his best to vacuum and changed the bedsheet every other day, it just couldn't keep up with the amount of dust collected every day.

The rest of the facilities is okay I guess, hot water is running, AC is cold enough, the housekeeper is also friendly and helpful.
review 2: The place is nice, the room is comfortable, and the sharing space is great, there's a shared kitchen too with free and every time something happened the owner are very responsive to resolve the problems. I had a very pleasant stay here for 5 weeks!

review 4:
Wow what an incredible place, all the ingredients are from locally sourced and mixoligist is very friendly, well articulated on each ingredient and its source.

The venue its self has excellent low lighting, jazz music a place to have a wonderful date or conversations with friends.

Its so refreshing to have such a wonderful place in Bali.
review 5: A unique place with a really brilliant experience in servicing, and the cocktails are ahh, can‚Äôt describe them without tasting them‚Ä¶ definitely 5 stars
